um%20tensor%20-%20a%20mathematical%20construct%20-%20to%20explain%20how%20energy%20and%20momentum%20are%20distributed%20in%20space-time%20and%20interact%20with%20the%20gravitational%20field.%20In%20Einstein's%20theory%20of%20gravity%2C%20the%20energy-momentum%20tensor%20is%20considered%20unchanged%2C%20or%20conserved.%20But%20a%20scientist%20from%20Russia%20has%20challenged%20this%20law%20of%20conservation%20presenting%20a%20new%20theory%20of%20gravity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20theory%20of%20relativity%20has%20its%20limitations%2C%20particularly%20at%20high%20energy%20levels%20where%20the%20so-called%20non-renormalisability%20problem%20arises.%20This%20means%20that%20mathematical%20flaws%20appear%20that%20cannot%20be%20eliminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20new%20theory%2C%20that%20counters%20Einstein's%2C%20Hamidreza%20Fazlollahi%2C%20a%20graduate%20student%20at%20the%20Educational%20and%20Scientific%20Institute%20of%20Gravity%20and%20Cosmology%20of%20RUDN%20University%2C%20claims%20to%20have%20found%20a%20solution%20to%20this%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20of%20non-renormalizability%20of%20Einstein's%20gravity%20is%20well%20known.%20It%20has%20led%20to%20dozens%20of%20attempts%20to%20treat%20it%20as%20a%20low-energy%20theory.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20string%20theory%2C%20Einstein's%20classical%20equation%20is%20just%20the%20first%20term%20in%20an%20infinite%20series%20of%20gravitational%20corrections%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Fazlollahi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newswise.com%2Farticles%2Frudn-astrophysicist-created-a-new-theory-of-gravity-without-a-conservation-law%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20at%20high%20energy%20and%2For%20within%20the%20event%20horizon%20of%20black%20holes%2C%20space-time%20curvature%20and%20gravity%20deviate%20from%20Einstein's%20general%20theory%20of%20relativity.%20This%20can%20be%20explained%20in%20different%20ways.%20However%2C%20in%20any%20case%2C%20the%20law%20of%20conservation%20of%20energy-momentum%20can%20be%20violated%20at%20high%20energy%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20new%20gravitational%20model%2C%20the%20researcher%20started%20from%20the%20so-called%20Gibbs-Duhem%20relation%20that%20is%20used%20in%20thermodynamics%20to%20describe%20changes%20in%20a%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resulting%20equation%20is%20similar%20to%20Einstein's%20but%20includes%20unique%20factors%20and%20constants%2C%20accounting%20for%20temperature-entropy%20and%20charge-interaction%20dynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Fazlollahi's%20model%20represents%20a%20significant%20step%20in%20understanding%20gravity%2C%20especially%20in%20extreme%20conditions%2C%20and%20could%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20new%20insights%20into%20the%20universe's%20mysteries.%20The%20model's%20alignment%20with%20experimental%20data%20suggests%20it%20could%20be%20a%20valuable%20tool%20for%20future%20research%20in%20astrophysics%20and%20cosmology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20is%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1140%2Fepjc%2Fs10052-023-12003-x%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20European%20Physical%20Journal%20C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706257500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-11%2F07pf5vb8_einstein-notes-theory-of-relativity-afp-650_625x300_24_November_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientist-counters-einsteins-relativity-theory-claims-hes-fixed-flaws-4935586%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20new%20gravitational%20model%2C%20the%20researcher%20started%20from%20the%20so-called%20Gibbs-Duhem%20relation%20that%20is%20used%20in%20thermodynamics%20to%20describe%20changes%20in%20a%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientist-counters-einstein