3Cspan%3EThose%20were%20simpler%20times.%20It%20was%20Pakistan%20who%20was%20the%20enemy%20even%20then%20%E2%80%93%20I%20vaguely%20remember%20dialogues%20ending%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejanaab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(good%20sir)%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20anywhere%20as%20cartoonish%20as%20this.%20In%202004%2C%20Roshan%20played%20a%20young%20man%20coming%20of%20age.%20In%202024%2C%20Roshan%20seems%20to%20have%20submitted%20to%20the%20pressures%20of%20stardom%20in%20a%20country%20where%20few%20things%20make%20sense.%20After%20resisting%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20Hrithik%20Roshan%E2%80%99s%20chiselled%20jawline%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20shred%20cheese%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20co-opted%20for%20the%20national%20cause.%20Roshan%2C%20who%20at%20one%20point%20was%20known%20to%20be%20obsessive%20about%20his%20image%2C%20refraining%20from%20doing%2Fsaying%20anything%20that%20might%20hurt%20his%20perfectly%20curated%20image%2C%20has%20sadly%20crossed%20over%20to%20the%20other%20side.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoshan%20spends%20the%20better%20part%20of%20the%20climactic%20showdown%20with%20the%20mastermind%20terrorist%20(Rishabh%20Sawhney)%20%E2%80%93%20telling%20him%20the%20many%20meanings%20of%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Hind%E2%80%99%20and%20making%20simplistic%2C%20pernicious%20claims%20about%20how%20Pakistan%20occupied%20Kashmir%20belongs%20to%20India.%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaalik%20hum%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E!%E2%80%9D%20(We%20own%20Kashmir!)%20he%20snarls%2C%20something%20that%20will%20no%20doubt%20be%20circulated%20as%20a%20clip%20via%20WhatsApp%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20And%20to%20think%20of%20a%20time%2C%20when%20a%20sincere%20version%20of%20the%20actor%20hobbled%20to%20a%20peak%2C%20hoisted%20the%20tricolour%20and%20sat%20on%20his%20knees%20while%20saluting%20it.%20It%20used%20to%20mean%20something.%20In%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20latest%2C%20Roshan%20appears%20with%20the%20tricolour%20from%20the%20chopper%2C%20and%20waves%20it%20at%20an%20Indian%20military%20convoy%2C%20which%20has%20death%20written%20all%20over%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F26114035%2FScreenshot-2024-01-26-at-11.39.3.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F26114035%2FScreenshot-2024-01-26-at-11.39.3.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F26114035%2FScreenshot-2024-01-26-at-11.39.3-300x126.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F26114035%2FScreenshot-2024-01-26-at-11.39.3-1024x429.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694470%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20Fighter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20surprisingly%2C%20a%20few%20scenes%20later%2C%20the%20convoy%20is%20bombed%20%E2%80%93%20like%20in%20Pulwama.%20What%E2%80%99s%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20tragic%20moment%2C%20becomes%20unexpectedly%20funny%20when%20director%20Anand%20rushes%20against%20time%20to%20%E2%80%98humanise%E2%80%99%20the%20soldiers%20sitting%20in%20the%20bus%20in%20less%20than%20a%20minute.%20One%20takes%20out%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eladdoo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20one%20abruptly%20talks%20about%20his%20mother%20and%20sister%2C%20and%20another%20one%20is%20on%20a%20video%20call%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20child.%20Manufacturing%20empathy%20for%20the%20simple-minded%2C%20gullible%20viewer%20in%20the%20laziest%20way%20possible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESiddharth%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFighter%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20features%20the%20greatest%20hits%20of%20everything%20that%E2%80%99s%20been%20terrible%20about%20the%20war%20film%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%20Long-haired%20terrorists%20hissing%20like%20snakes%2C%20Pakistani%20army%20bumbling%20like%20they%E2%80%99re%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%20Minister%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20local%20Kashmiri%20youth%20carrying%20knives%20and%20stones%20in%20their%20palms%2C%20politicians%20blaming%20earlier%20governments%20for%20their%20sane%20temperament%20and%20talking%20about%20a%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emooh%20tod%20jawab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20neighbours%2C%20the%20skull-cap%20wearing%20parent%20of%20a%20slain%20soldier%20talking%20about%20how%20%E2%80%98watan%E2%80%99%20(nation)%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20for%20a%20believer%2C%20and%20soldiers%20fantasising%20about%20the%20tricolour%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98kafan%E2%80%99%20(shroud)%20for%20their%20martyred%20bodies.%20Above%20all%2C%20A-list%20star%20power%20to%20legitimise%20all%20this.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPatty%20or%20Shamsher%20Pathania%20(Roshan)%20is%20Pete%20Mitchell%20(Tom%20Cruise%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ETop%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EGun%3C%2Fem%3E%20movies)%2C%20seen%20through%20a%20saffron%20lens.%20He%E2%80%99s%20confident%2C%20cocky%2C%20and%20hated%20by%20his%20superiors.%20He%E2%80%99s%20a%20part%20of%20a%20Top%20Gun-esque%20outfit%20for%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%20which%20comprises%20the%20best.%20Patty%20is%20accompanied%20by%20fighter%20jet%20pilots%20%E2%80%93%20Taj%20or%20Sartaj%20Gill%20(Karan%20Singh%20Grover)%2C%20Bash%20or%20Basheer%20Khan%20(an%20easy-to-watch%20Akshay%20Oberoi)%2C%20who%20says%20something%20about%20reaching%20%E2%80%98jannat%E2%80%99%20in%20his%20first%20scene%2C%20which%20you%20know%20is%20bad%20foreshadowing.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMinni%20or%20Minal%20Rathore