20have%20lost%20faith%20in%20the%20present%20system%20of%20conducting%20elections%20using%20EVMs.%E2%80%9D%20This%20group%20will%20be%20looking%20at%20issues%20other%20than%20EVMs%2C%20such%20as%20those%20raised%20by%20the%20CCE%20including%20flaws%20in%20the%20electoral%20rolls%20and%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20way%20to%20conduct%20elections%20is%20paper%20ballots%20if%20the%20trust%20deficit%20is%20to%20be%20bridged%2C%20Pitroda%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20civil%20society%20has%20repeatedly%20been%20petitioning%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20either%20go%20back%20to%20paper%20ballots%20or%20to%20do%20a%20100%25%20count%20of%20the%20VVPAT%20slips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20about%20pushing%20for%20digital%20India.%20It%20is%20about%20going%20back%20to%20the%20fundamentals%2C%20going%20back%20to%20paper.%20And%20the%202024%20election%20will%20decide%20the%20destiny%20of%20the%20nation%20for%20a%20long%20time%20to%20come.%20The%20voter%20no%20longer%20knows%20whom%20to%20trust%20where%20EVMs%20and%20VVPATs%20are%20concerned.%20We%20have%20to%20convince%20the%20voter%2C%20not%20the%20ECI%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20The%20ECI%20has%20been%20steadfast%20in%20its%20refusal%20to%20address%20the%20concerns%20of%20civil%20society%20even%20though%20the%20concerns%20raised%20in%20the%20CCE%20report%20are%20alarming%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20questions%20whether%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20would%20be%20urged%20to%20add%20this%20demand%20of%20paper%20ballots%20to%20their%20manifestos%2C%20Pitroda%2C%20who%20said%20he%20is%20speaking%20as%20an%20Indian%20citizen%20and%20not%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CManifestos%20come%20in%20the%20end.%20This%20problem%20has%20to%20be%20solved%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20opposition%20is%20not%20speaking%20in%20one%20voice%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20EVMs%20Pitroda%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20advice%20to%20the%20opposition%20is%20to%20wake%20up.%20But%20it%20is%20for%20the%20opposition%20parties%20to%20answer%20as%20to%20how%20they%20intend%20to%20take%20up%20an%20issue%20that%20affects%20them%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECCE%20convenor%20M.G.%20Devasahayam%20said%20various%20citizens%E2%80%99%20groups%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20draw%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20ECI%20to%20concerns%20about%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20elections%20but%20to%20little%20avail.%20He%20said%20the%20CCE%20report%20put%20together%20by%20global%20experts%20in%20the%20fields%20of%20computer%20science%20and%20electronics%20has%20clearly%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20absence%20of%20end-to-end%20verifiability%20of%20the%20voting%20process%20the%20present%20system%20is%20unfit%20for%20democratic%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDevasahayam%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20practice%2C%20there%20is%20a%20requirement%20for%20100%25%20counting%20of%20VVPAT%20slips.%20The%20system%20should%20be%20software%20and%20hardware-independent%20to%20be%20verifiable%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20German%20Supreme%20Court%20threw%20out%20EVMs%20and%20declared%20unconstitutional%20any%20electoral%20process%20that%20does%20not%20comply%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20democracy%20and%20end-to-end%20verifiability%20meaning%20the%20voter%20should%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20verify%20her%20vote%20has%20been%20cast%20as%20intended%20and%20recorded%20as%20cast.%20That%20is%20not%20happening%20in%20the%20present%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECriticising%20critics%20who%20say%20paper%20ballots%20are%20a%20long%20tedious%20process%20of%20counting%2C%20Devashayam%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20takes%20weeks%2C%20if%20not%20months%20to%20conduct%20an%20election.%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20counting%20process%2C%20they%20are%20in%20a%20tearing%20hurry%20and%20want%20to%20get%20over%20the%20counting%20process%20in%20a%20hurry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Pitroda%20and%20Devashayam%20said%20the%20issue%20is%20no%20longer%20about%20whether%20the%20system%20can%20be%20hacked%20or%20the%20lack%20of%20transparency%20or%20the%20software%20used.%20The%20issue%2C%20they%20said%2C%20is%20to%20revive%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20people%20in%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706203528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09193848%2FScreenshot-2023-11-09-at-7.38.08%25E2%2580%25AFPM_cleanup.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsam-pitroda-civil-society-to-put-in-place-an-independent-expert-panel-to-monitor-2024-polls%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Noting%20that%20the%20citizens%20have%20lost%20faith%20in%20the%20present%20system%20of%20conducting%20elections%20using%20EVMs%2C%20Citizens'%20Commission%20on%20Elections%20said%20a%20seven-member%20committee%20will%20'keep%20a%20watch%20on%20elections'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsam-pitroda-civil-society-to-put-in-place-an-independent-expert-panel-to-monitor-2024-polls%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Malicious%20Propaganda'%3A%20India%20Refutes%20Pakistan's%20Accusations%20of%20Involvement%20in%20Targeted%20Killings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F18215053%2Findia-pakistan-flag.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20on%20Thursday%2C%20January%2025%2C%20strongly%20rejected%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20assertion%20of%20evidence%20implicating%20Indian%20agents%20in%20the%20targeted%20killings%20of%20two%20Pakistani%20citizens%20on%20its%20soil%2C%20dismissing%20it%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20and%20malicious%20anti-India%20propaganda%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1808549%2Fcredible-evidence-of-links-between-indian-agents-and-assassination-of-2-pakistanis-foreign-secretary%5C%22%3EAt%20a%20media%20conference%20in%20Islamabad%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pakistan%20foreign%20secretary%20Muhammad%20Syrus%20Sajjad%20Qazi%20said%20that%20India%20was%20running%20a%20campaign%20of%20%E2%80%9Cextra-territorial%20and%20extra-judicial%20killings%E2%80%9D%20and%20had%20set%20up%20a%20%E2%80%9Csophisticated%20international%20set-up%20spread%20over%20multiple%20jurisdictions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20to%20the%20allegations%20made%20by%20Canada%20and%20the%20United%20States%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20network%20of%20extra-judicial%20and%20extra-territorial%20killings%20has%20become%20a%20global%20phenomenon%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQazi%20said%20that%20investigation%20had%20found%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20linking%20Indian%20agents%2C%20identified%20as%20Yogesh%20Kumar%20and%20Ashok%20Kumar%20Anand%2C%20with%20the%20killing%20of%20Muhammad%20Riaz%20in%20September%202023%20and%20Shahid%20Latif%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20dismissed%20the%20Pakistani%20allegations.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20media%20reports%20regarding%20certain%20remarks%20by%20Pakistan%20Foreign%20Secretary.%20It%20is%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20latest%20attempt%20at%20peddling%20false%20and%20malicious%20anti-India%20propaganda%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fresponse-to-queries.htm%3Fdtl%2F37532%2FOfficial_Spokespersons_response_to_media_queries_regarding_remarks_made_by_Pakistan_Foreign_Ministry%5C%22%3Esaid%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asserted%20that%20Pakistan%20has%20long%20been%20known%20worldwide%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20epicentre%20of%20terrorism%2C%20organised%20crime%2C%20and%20illegal%20transnational%20activities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20and%20many%20other%20countries%20have%20publicly%20warned%20Pakistan%20cautioning%20that%20it%20would%20be%20consumed%20by%20its%20own%20culture%20of%20terror%20and%20violence.%20Pakistan%20will%20reap%20what%20it%20sows.%20To%20blame%20others%20for%20its%20own%20misdeeds%20can%20neither%20be%20a%20justification%20nor%20a%20solution%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20foreign%20secretary%20alleged%20that%20Indian%20agents%20%E2%80%9Crecruited%2C%20financed%20and%20supported%20criminals%2C%20terrorists%20and%20unsuspecting%20civilians%20to%20play%20defined%20roles%20in%20these%20assassinations%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevidence%E2%80%9D%20was%20confessions%20from%20the%20alleged%20hitmen%20and%20money%20transfers%20into%20their%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20Indian%20media%20and%20social%20media%20accounts%20promptly%20celebrated%20the%20killing%20of%20the%20two%20men%20as%20%E2%80%9Csuccessful%20retribution%20against%20enemies%20of%20India%20and%20projected%20their%20capacity%20to%20carry%20out%20these%20illegal%20acts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Qazi%20referred%20to%20a%20Muhammad%20Riaz%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Findia-shahid-latif-hardeep-nijjar-terrorists-attacked-killed-pakistan-nepal-canada-2447590-2023-10-11%5C%22%3EIndian%20media%20had%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20September%20about%20the%20killing%20of%20Riyaz%20Ahmad%2C%20a%20Lashkar-e-Toiba%20member%2C%20at%20Rawalkot%20in%20September%202023.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Fworld%2Fstory%2Fpathankot-attack-mastermind-shahid-latif-shot-dead-by-unidentified-assailants-401506-2023-10-11%5C%22%3ELatif%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Jaish-e-Mohhammed%20and%20described%20as%20a%20mastermind%20of%20the%20terror%20attack%20on%20the%20Pathankot%20air%20base%2C%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20a%20mosque%20at%20Sialkot%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQazi%20additionally%20connected%20the%20killings%20in%20Pakistan%20to%20a%20perceived%20pattern%20of%20purported%20actions%20by%20Indian%20agents%20in%20Canada%20and%20the%20US.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20killing%20of%20a%20Sikh%20leader%20in%20Canada%20is%20just%20one%20example%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20operations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20must%20be%20held%20accountable%20internationally%20for%20its%20blatant%20violation%20of%20international%20law.%20India%E2%80%99s%20assassination%20of%20Pakistani%20nationals%20on%20Pakistani%20soil%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20its%20sovereignty%20and%20a%20breach%20of%20the%20UN%20charter%2C%E2%80%9D%20Qazi%20asserted%2C%20adding%20that%20Pakistan%20reserved%20the%20right%20to%20approach%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20and%20other%20fora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20September%2C%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20had%20said%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%E2%80%9D%20intelligence%20of%20Indian%20government%20agents%20being%20behind%20the%20shooting%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20Harpreet%20Singh%20Nijjar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20announced%20a%20potential%20connection%20between%20the%20killing%20of%20Nijjar%20and%20the%20thwarting%20of%20a%20plot%20to%20assassinate%20a%20Canadian-American%20Khalistani%20supporter%20in%20New%20York%20through%20an%20unsealed%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20Indian%20national%2C%20Nikhil%20Gupta%2C%20currently%20in%20Czech%20custody%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20hiring%20a%20hitman%2C%20who%20was%20actually%20an%20undercover%20operative%2C%20on%20the%20instructions%20of%20an%20Indian%20government%20agent%20to%20kill%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannu%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%2C%20a%20group%20banned%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20had%20angrily%20dismissed%20the%20accusations%20by%20Canada%2C%20a%20top-level%20